# Testing Rules

## Framework
- Unit tests: Vitest
- E2E tests: Playwright (later phase)
- No Jest — use Vitest exclusively

## Test File Conventions
- Co-located tests in `__tests__/` directories
- Name: `<module>.test.ts`
- Use `describe` blocks matching the module name
- Use `it` (not `test`) for individual cases
- Descriptive test names: `it('should return empty array when API returns 404')`

## API Testing Pattern
```typescript
// Always use fixtures, never live calls
import fixture from './fixtures/gdelt-response.json';
import { normalize } from '../normalizer';

describe('gdelt normalizer', () => {
  it('should normalize valid response to LebanonEvent[]', () => {
    const events = normalize(fixture);
    expect(events).toHaveLength(expect.any(Number));
    events.forEach(event => {
      expect(event.source).toBe('gdelt');
      expect(event.latitude).toBeGreaterThan(33);
      expect(event.latitude).toBeLessThan(35);
      expect(event.longitude).toBeGreaterThan(35);
      expect(event.longitude).toBeLessThan(37);
      expect(['lumiere', 'ombre', 'neutre']).toContain(event.classification);
    });
  });
});
```

## Validation Checklist (run after each source is built)
For each source, verify:
- [ ] API call returns valid data (save fixture)
- [ ] Normalizer produces correct LebanonEvent shape
- [ ] All events have valid lat/lng within Lebanon bounding box
- [ ] Classification produces reasonable lumiere/ombre distribution
- [ ] Error handling works (test with invalid params, timeout)
- [ ] TTL/caching behaves correctly
- [ ] TypeScript compiles with no errors
